    "short_description": "A 15th-century heritage hotel spread over 14 levels on the Aravalli hills.",
    "long_description": "Neemrana Fort-Palace is India's oldest heritage hotel, built in 1464 AD. It is a stunning architectural feat, cut into the Aravalli hill and spread over 14 tiers. Once the capital of the descendants of Prithviraj Chauhan III, it stood in ruins for decades before being restored in 1991 into a majestic hotel.\n\nThe fort offers a labyrinth of experiences with its hanging gardens, ayurvedic spa, and two swimming pools. It is famous for launching India's first zip-line tour. The rooms are furnished with an eclectic mix of traditional Indian and colonial furniture, and no two rooms are alike. It is a popular destination for those seeking a quick but complete immersion into Rajasthan's royal past.",
